<lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">vṛṣa</hi> varu<hi rend="grantha">ṣa</hi>m paṅkuṉi mā<hi rend="grantha">sa</hi>m 4 poṉ pattaṅki Appaiyaṅkā<supplied reason="omitted">r</supplied> pāyyi<note n="150-4">This word seems to be the corruption of <hi rend="italic">bhārya.</hi></note>Āccamaneṉ rekunātapperumā
<lb n="2" break="no"/>ḷ kaiṅkariyam polive<hi rend="grantha">ṭṭi</hi> ciṟappukku camaṟppitta poṉṉu[ <hi rend="grantha">kk</hi>u] m nellu[ <hi rend="grantha">kk</hi>u] m viparāmacakkiṟavatti rāmayaṅkār 
<lb n="3"/>pu<note n="151-1">This is a symbol for paṇam</note> <hi rend="grantha">ṭṭi</hi> yintappaṇa muppatu[ <hi rend="grantha">kk</hi>u] m <hi rend="grantha">(1/4)<num value="30">3 <g type="numeral">10</g></num></hi> varu<hi rend="grantha">ṣā</hi>vati pu4<note n="151-1">This is a symbol for paṇam</note> yinta pu4[ <hi rend="grantha">kk</hi>u] m Āvaṇi <unclear>m</unclear>āta<unclear>tti</unclear>l
<lb n="4"/>paṟvattil Appayaṅkār tiruvattiruciṟappu camaṟppi<hi rend="grantha">kka</hi>vu<hi rend="grantha">m</hi>
<lb n="5"/><hi rend="grantha">svā</hi>mi kāriyattil yātām Oruvar vikātam coṉ<note n="151-2">Written above the line.</note>ṉālum ciṟappu camppiyāviṭṭālum Avaṉ tām toppainaiyu<hi rend="grantha">m</hi><note n="151-3">the intended text is apparently taṉ mātā takappaṉaiyum</note> Ācāriyanaiyu<hi rend="grantha">m</hi> kārām pacuvaiyu<hi rend="grantha">m</hi>
<lb n="6"/>keṅka karaiyil koṉṉato<hi rend="grantha">ṣa</hi>ttil poka
<lb n="7"/><unclear>ka</unclear>ṭavaṉ <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied>
